Primary Outcome Measures:
Genetic basis of beta cell function, Investigators genotype diabetes risk loci and relate them to two main beta cell metrics, after correction for insulin sensitivity:

1. Derivative control of beta cell function: it is the amount of insulin secreted in response to a rate of glucose increase of 1 mmol/l per min which lasts for 1 minute;
2. Proportional control of beta cell function: it is the stimulus-response curve linking glucose concentration (x-axis) to insulin secretion rate (y-axis) at the preselected glucose concentrations of 5.5, 8.0, 11.0, 15.0, and 20.0 mmol/liter., Baseline and during the 75 g oral glucose challenge. Subjects will be followed for the duration of their stay in the Metabolic Clinical Research Center (average expected stay: 6 hours)
